Lagos – Major-General Shuaibu Ibrahim, the Director General of the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC), on Tuesday, commended the House of Representatives, especially the House Committee on Youth Development, for the speedy hearing on the proposed NYSC Trust Fund. The DG stated this inanation wide message delivered across the 36 states and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), Abujna orientation camps for the swearing- in ceremony of the 2022 Batch ‘A’ stream 1 corps members. The DG, in the message read by the Ogun State Coordinator of the NYSC, Dr. Belinda Faniyi, thanked Nigerians for the continuous show of support for the proposed Trust Fund, especially as overwhelmingly demonstrated during the public hearing conducted by the House Committee on Youth on the matter. Lagos Partners GIZ On Improving Ease of Doing Business,… Port Protests: Customs Delegation Visits Lagos, Examines Agents’… At the swearing-in ceremony for over 1,700 corps members, which was held at the Permanent Orientation Camp, Sagamu International Stadium, Major-General Shuaibu Ibrahim said the NYSC Trust Fund.